1) ISSUE: Orphaned items in the Held POs card did not indicate which supplier each item belongs to.

   ROOT CAUSE:
   - The held orphaned-item card rendered product/price/qty metadata only.
   - Supplier information was available in the item object but not displayed in the card UI.

   RESOLUTION IMPLEMENTED:
   - Updated held-item card text in the Restock Workflow UI to explicitly include supplier name.
   - New label pattern:
     `Supplier: <supplier name> · Qty <n> · Unit <amount> · Total <amount>`
   - Falls back to `Unknown supplier` when supplier details are absent.

   HOW TO VERIFY:
   A) UI check
      - Go to Admin → Restock Management → Purchase Orders tab → On Hold status.
      - Ensure each “Held item …” card now visibly includes `Supplier: ...`.
   B) Data variance check
      - Confirm cards with normal supplier links show a real supplier name.
      - Confirm edge-case records without supplier relation display `Unknown supplier` gracefully.
   C) Regression check
      - Ensure “Create request and link to PO” action still works exactly as before.


2) ISSUE: Restock management modals resized by content instead of using a consistent fixed max modal size.

   ROOT CAUSE:
   - Multiple modal variants used different max-width classes (`max-w-lg`, `max-w-2xl`, `max-w-3xl`, `max-w-4xl`).
   - This caused visual “size jumping” depending on which modal was opened and content density.

   RESOLUTION IMPLEMENTED:
   - Standardized restock workflow modal containers to a single fixed max width:
     `w-full max-w-4xl ...`
   - Retained viewport-constrained vertical behavior (`max-h[...]` + `overflow-y-auto`) so dialogs scale with screen size only.
   - Result: modal footprint is now consistent while still responsive to viewport dimensions.

   HOW TO VERIFY:
   A) Cross-modal consistency
      - Open each of these dialogs in sequence and compare width:
        - Generate PO
        - Place PO
        - Edit PO
        - Receive PO
        - Request details
        - Supplier request list modal
        - Supplier PO list modal
        - Release from hold modal
        - PO details modal
      - Confirm all use same maximum width and no “narrow vs wide” jumping remains.
   B) Viewport behavior
      - Resize browser from desktop to smaller laptop/tablet widths.
      - Confirm modal width scales down responsively and content scrolls internally rather than overflowing screen.
   C) Padding/layout integrity
      - Confirm spacing and button alignment remain intact across all modal types.


3) ISSUE: Supplier cards in Current Requests did not show “order placed” context even when linked requests were on a placed PO.

   ROOT CAUSE:
   - Supplier summary cards only displayed “linked to <open PO number>” using open-PO lookup.
   - They did not include a status signal derived from request-level `requestLinkedToPlacedPo(...)` state.

   RESOLUTION IMPLEMENTED:
   - Added an aggregate supplier-card badge:
     `Order placed`
   - Badge is shown when any request in that supplier group satisfies placed-PO linkage logic.
   - This aligns supplier-card summary state with request-card status badges.

   HOW TO VERIFY:
   A) Functional check
      - Go to Current Requests.
      - For a supplier group with at least one request linked to a placed PO, verify the supplier card displays `Order placed` badge.
   B) Negative check
      - For supplier groups without any placed-link request, verify the badge is absent.
   C) Consistency check
      - Open that supplier group / request details and confirm request-level status indicators match the supplier-card summary badge.


4) ISSUE: Purchase Order print flow failed when browser blocked popups.

   ROOT CAUSE:
   - Printing relied on `window.open(...)` for a new tab/window.
   - Popup blockers commonly block this mechanism, preventing print dialog launch.

   RESOLUTION IMPLEMENTED:
   - Replaced popup-dependent print flow with hidden iframe-based printing.
   - New flow:
     1. Create off-screen iframe.
     2. Write PO HTML into iframe document.
     3. Trigger print on iframe window.
     4. Clean up iframe after print trigger.
   - This avoids opening a popup window and is resilient in popup-blocked environments.

   HOW TO VERIFY:
   A) Browser-level popup-block scenario
      - Enable strict popup blocking in browser settings.
      - Open a PO detail modal and click “Print Purchase Order”.
      - Confirm print dialog still opens.
   B) Smoke check
      - Verify generated print layout still includes PO number, supplier, status, total, and item table.
   C) Repeated invocation check
      - Trigger print multiple times on same/different POs.
      - Confirm no visible orphan windows/tabs are created and no UI degradation occurs.


